Zuboff, S. (2019). The age of surveillance capitalism. PublicAffairs. — The major treatment of how behavioral data extraction became the dominant business model of the internet era. The chapter’s argument about conversational AI as extraction technology sits in this lineage.
Cohen, J. E. (2019). Between truth and power: The legal constructions of informational capitalism. Oxford University Press. — On how legal and regulatory structures have failed to address the deeper architecture of data extraction.
Crawford, K. (2021). Atlas of AI: Power, politics, and the planetary costs of artificial intelligence. Yale University Press. — Material treatment of AI as infrastructure dependent on labor, minerals, and data extraction. (Also cited in the previous chapter’s bibliography.)
